<div class="c230_110">
<div id="v230.110.1"><span class="H4210 s">A Psalm</span><span class="H1732 s"> of David</span><span class="H3068 s">. The LORD</span><span class="H5002 s"> said</span><span class="H113 s"> unto my Lord</span><span class="H3427 s">, Sit</span><span class="H3225 s"> thou at my right hand</span><span class="H7896 s">, until I make</span><span class="H341 s"> thine enemies</span><span class="H1916 s"> thy footstool</span><span class="H7272 s"> †</span>.</div>
<div id="v230.110.2"><span class="H3068 s">The LORD</span><span class="H7971 s"> shall send</span><span class="H4294 s"> the rod</span><span class="H5797 s"> of thy strength</span><span class="H6726 s"> out of Zion</span><span class="H7287 s">: rule</span><span class="H7130 s"> thou in the midst</span><span class="H341 s"> of thine enemies</span>.</div>
<div id="v230.110.3"><span class="H5971 s">Thy people</span><span class="H5071 s"> <i>shall be</i> willing</span><span class="H3117 s"> in the day</span><span class="H2428 s"> of thy power</span><span class="H1926 s">, in the beauties</span><span class="H6944 s"> of holiness</span><span class="H7358 s"> from the womb</span><span class="H4891 s"> of the morning</span><span class="H2919 s">: thou hast the dew</span><span class="H3208 s"> of thy youth</span>. <span class="notes">Notes by the 1611 King James Bible Translators: (from…: or, more than the womb of the morning: thou shalt have, etc)</span></div>
<div id="v230.110.4"><span class="H3068 s">The LORD</span><span class="H7650 s"> hath sworn</span><span class="H5162 s">, and will not repent</span><span class="H3548 s">, Thou <i>art</i> a priest</span><span class="H5769 s"> for ever</span><span class="H1700 s"> after the order</span><span class="H4442 s"> of Melchizedek</span>.</div>
<div id="v230.110.5"><span class="H136 s">The Lord</span><span class="H3225 s"> at thy right hand</span><span class="H4272 s"> shall strike</span><span class="H4428 s"> through kings</span><span class="H3117 s"> in the day</span><span class="H639 s"> of his wrath</span>.</div>
<div id="v230.110.6"><span class="H1777 s">He shall judge</span><span class="H1471 s"> among the heathen</span><span class="H4390 s">, he shall fill</span><span class="H1472 s"> <i>the places</i> with the dead bodies</span><span class="H4272 s">; he shall wound</span><span class="H7218 s"> the heads</span><span class="H7227 s"> over many</span><span class="H776 s"> countries</span>. <span class="notes">Notes by the 1611 King James Bible Translators: (many: or, great)</span></div>
<div id="v230.110.7"><span class="H8354 s">He shall drink</span><span class="H5158 s"> of the brook</span><span class="H1870 s"> in the way</span><span class="H7311 s">: therefore shall he lift up</span><span class="H7218 s"> the head</span>.</div></div>
